<Author>KeepDiscovering
<Content>Good location, compact room, helpful staff, wonderful freebies I stayed in Ramada Kowloon for 1 night during my transit back to the Middle East. The hotel's undoubtful advantage was its location. I took a bus (A21 or A22 I can't remember clearly) from the airport and 40 min later it stopped in front of the hotel! The bus stop back to airport is just on the opposite side of the road. So very handy for transit passengers like me.I got a room upgrade (standard - something better) when check-in. The room was small, layout was odd (my room was located in a corner of a V-shaped building) but clean. The bed was huge. Nevertheless, other furniture was still basic, so I wondered that if this room was the upgraded one, then standard rooms would be very ordinary.There were many restaurants near to the hotel so there's no difficulty looking for food. For shopping, I would prefer walking to Canton Road though. Choices of food in the hotel restaurant were very limited.Staff was friendly and helpful (esp w/ the upgrade). I asked for a late checkout (as I took an evening flight) and they could grand me one right away. 
