<Content>Good hotel in an unbeatable location I stayed here for 10 days and I liked it. My room was overlooking the street with large glass windows (window cannot be opened). I enjoyed the view. The room was basic and small. But it was adequate. The bathroom was also basic. But it was very clean. The breakfast was OK, but got somewhat boring towards end of my stay as they repeat the same stuff. I had dinner once here, I did not like it. But there are plenty of food options as soon as you step out of the hotel. The location is unbeatable. It is in the heart of tourist district of TST in Kowloon. The bus-stop is right outside the hotel. The metro is within easy walking distance. There is also an airport shuttle that you can book from the hotel. The best part is that the staff was very friendly and helpful. There is a small business center where you can get print outs and access the Internet. There is also a travel desk who helped me with visas for mainland China. It is a budget sort of hotel. But I believe that I got more than my money worth. 
