<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Good value for Hong Kong I stayed at the Ramada for four nights in January and thought it was OK. It certainly is in need of redecoration, and my room was a little cramped. However, it was clean and decent; the staff were nice and friendly; and the location is excellent: a block or two to the TST MRT station; frequent buses to the Star Ferry and the airport going past the door; and the shops and restaurants of the Nathan Road area just around the corner. The buffet meals were not exciting but were quite adequate. I paid $HK550 a night (plus taxes), which is very good value for Hong Kong. This is a good place for the budget traveller who wants something better than a backpackers' guesthouse (and who can't get into the Y!). 
