<Content>A budget hotel We stayed at Ramada Kowloon Hotel for 5 days. It was an ok budget hotel, nothing fancy. The room was small (as in any other hotel rooms in Hong Kong) and we don't have a view (our room is on the 4th floor). We don't mind this because we spent our time outside. Despite these, the room  toilet were clean, no complaints there. I noticed that the room door  bathroom door need a little fixing, but they still work. Elevator is small as well as the lobby. Hotel staff were friendly and helpful. The location is a little far going to the harbour, but it was nice walking around TST. You also need to walk a little far to reach the MTR station. There are shops nearby that sells clothes, shoes, bags, food, etc. Nice! We didn't eat at the restaurant because there were fast food restaurants nearby. All in all, the hotel is ok for travellers who just need a nice, clean room to stay after going around Hong Kong. 
